OL,3,CMagistrates told to delay sentencing
OL,4,Cto ease prison overcrowding
OL,6,FMark Fairhurst, national chairman of
OL,7,Fthe Prison Officers' Association
OL,8,F(POA), said: "POA members are the only
OL,9,Fpeople who have absolutely no
OL,10,Finvolvement in the incarceration of
OL,11,Findividuals.
OL,13,F"We do not arrest, investigate,
OL,14,Fcharge, convict or sentence. We will,
OL,15,Fhowever, stand ready to accept those
OL,16,Fwho are sent to us by the courts.
OL,18,F"We can accommodate anyone who is
OL,19,Fconvicted, so we see no reason why
OL,20,Fjustice should be delayed."
